{
  "text": "The LQTS patients for whom cardiac pacing is indicated are very few. In infants or young children with 2:1 AV block this remains a reasonable choice, as a bridge to the ICD. The fact that the onset of TdP is very often preceded by a pause [CITATION_1] might add to the rationale of using a pacemaker as an adjunct to the therapy of some LQTS patients. However, nowadays if a pacemaker is being considered, it is probably more logical to implant an ICD with pacing modes. In any case, pacemakers should never be used as a sole therapy for LQTS.",
